==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Induction motor
<hw>Induction motor</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A type of
alternating-current motor comprising two wound members, one stationary,
called the <part>stator</part>, and the other rotating, called the
<part>rotor</part>, these two members corresponding to a certain extent
to the field and armature of a direct-current motor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inductive</ent>⟦br⟧
